node.accessibility_caption: Photo by California Barber - Vinnie ✪ in Orange, California with @illuzien, @shauntopper, @valleyeyewear, and @establishedkraft. May be an image of 2 people and beard.

node.text: Being a barber or a stylist isn’t about being seen or being cool, it’s about taking care of your community! Fall in love with the craft and the craft will take care of you in return! Get out of it what you put into it! Stand and grind! I can not express enough how amazing @establishedkraft work is, he captures the passion of this trade and I am honored to have been frozen in time by him! I appreciate you my brother #getestablished

node.text: This reconnection is exactly what so many of us needed, there was education and competition and that is beautiful, but above all it was being back with the industry we love and the people that make it so amazing! Thank you @jay_majors for 10 years of giving, people forget how much competing at a battle can do for their career and past that how much the @connecticutbarberexpo does for the industry! To the rest of my family I love you and appreciate you all more than words! @babylisspro_barberology

node.text: Yes this weekend was the @connecticutbarberexpo and it was absolutely amazing, it felt great to be back at a show and feel that energy again! Beyond that, for me…. It was reconnecting with family and one member of that family was for sure with us and will always be with us on every stage at every show we brought the kid with us! @judgernaut4 you are a giant and your absence hurts but your joy and memory filled a little piece this weekend! I can’t thank @dennisjosephbabyliss enough for building this family and for keeping us whole, @magally79 you are the constant for this family as well! @babylisspro_barberology is so much more than a brand what these people have built will live on far past clippers or dryers, they gift these memories and those are priceless! @stamstock thank you for being right there with us and letting this wild machine run! #judgeforever

node.text: These 4 walls, they hold laughter, joy, sadness, pain, victory, defeat, creativity, love and so much more, these 4 walls hold me up, these 4 walls give life to so many and enrich those who dare to step inside. A barbershop is so much more than a place to get a haircut, this is therapy, celebration, comfort, bonding, this is a community! I hold these 4 walls so tight because to me they are sacred!
